NOTE:  The mailbox petfinder sends the "Ask About" email inquiries to is not as closely monitored as the email address applications go to.   That feature is a default with petfinder, and is not a part of our adoption process.

The first step in our adoption process is the application.  Completed applications take priority over inquiries.  To apply to adopt, please copy and paste the following url:

https://fs30.formsite.com/legacygsd/form4/index.html

Introducing Copper!  Copper is a Bloodhound. He is 31/2yrs old and weighs around 110lbs. 

Copper was an owner surrender. His previous owners couldn't provide basic care for him and agreed it would be in his best interest to give him to rescue that could find him a forever home.

Copper is a kind, patient, noble, mild-mannered and lovable dog.  He is all hound and can sing the song of his people.  He can be very boisterous at times, especially if other dogs near by are barking. He enjoys playing outside on pretty days with his buddy Jack.  He has been out and about with other dogs around his size and done well.  He can be pretty energetic outside when out with friends. If he gets a case of the zoomies watch out! You don't want 110lbs of dog running up on you.  Copper can be stubborn from time to time so he needs an owner that will provide consistent training and calm/assertive leadership.  Because Bloodhounds are born to work, Copper will need physical and mental stimulation.  Daily walks or interactive toys and regular play time will keep him from getting bored.  Copper isn't the greatest on a leash if he catches a scent he needs to investigate. He could use some more leash work to master loose leash walking. In general, Copper is a gentle giant who wants to love and be loved.  Copper has been around children 12yrs and up.  He can be cat tested upon request.  He will need an active family with a fenced yard. 

Copper is up to date on vaccines, has been tested for heartworm and 5 diseases spread by ticks, was treated for heartworm disease and has gotten a clean bill of health, is neutered and microchipped. Copper is on monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention.

As with all of our dogs, we recommend a basic obedience class to help him understand what is expected of him, and this also helps with the bonding process. 

Copper's adoption fee is $475, which covers all his vetting, preventatives, fostering costs and other associated expenses.  We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

https://fs30.formsite.com/legacygsd/form4/index.html

Introducing Dixie! Dixie is a Dachshund mix.  She turned 10 yrs young on February 1st. Dixie weighs 17lbs.

Dixie was a trucking dog.  She traveled the lower 48 for the last 9 1/2 yrs. Her dad lost his job due to covid.  When he finally got picked up by another company they said no dogs allowed in the trucks. He had no choice but to let his beloved Dixie go.  I promised him I'd find her a wonderful home for her to live out her golden years. 

Dixie is a sweet girl.  She loves to cuddle on the couch and is always up for a Criminal Minds marathon.   She is a typical Dachshund.  Inquisitive, smart, and very engaged.  She is nose to the ground to take in all the smells when she's in a new place.  She obviously rides well and is always up for an adventure.  She can be a little shy at first but warns up quickly.  She's very treat motivated.  Dixie is house (well truck cab) trained.  She doesn't make messes in her kennel but doesn't really care for it and sometimes will bark to show her displeasure when in it.  She really doesn't need it.  She's very well mannered.  Dixie has been around other dogs and has done fine.  She used to have a *sister* that rode in the truck too. She is fine on a leash but does like to investigate everything so she will pull but she's small and easy to control.   Dixie has met the resident cat and was unimpressed.  She's been around children 12 and up.  She's never been around young children.

Dixie is fully vetted and up to date on vaccines, she's been tested for heartworms and 5 diseases spread by ticks, is spayed and microchipped.  She had mammary tumors removed at the time of her spay but they were benign.

Dixie's adoption fee is $475, which covers all her vetting, preventatives, fostering costs and other associated expenses.  We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Chief is a cute fuzzy Husky/German Shepherd mix puppy with a charming personality.  He arrived at the shelter along with his sisters, Heidi and Kira; who have already been adopted.  Chief is fourteen weeks old and ready to find his new forever home.  This cuddly little teddy bear weighs just twelve pounds but will be a large dog someday.  Sweet, rambunctious and playful, he would make a perfect companion for a family with children.  He needs someone that has the time to raise and train a puppy.  Chief is just beginning to learn his doggie ABC’s and is not housebroken.  A fenced in yard will help with house training and give him a safe place to run and play.  Chief would enjoy having another dog to play with in his new home.  He is also to perfect age to learn to be respectful around cats.  Chief is simply adorable and will make a fabulous family pet.  

To adopt this pet, Click "More About Us" and then "Adoption Application" to be directed to our online HSNWGA application form.  You will be contacted by our Adoption Coordinator once your application is reviewed and approved.  Due to high volume of applications, we are only able to contact those applicants that best meet the needs of that individual pet.

Beanie was an owner surrender.  Someone got him at 6 weeks old and didn't realize the cost and responsibility involved with raising a puppy. They surrendered him so we can find him a forever home.

Simba is a sweet terrier mix, 3 years old and weighs about 13 lbs.  Her previous owner passed away and left her and 6 other dogs with no home and no other family to take care of her.

We believe she had not been exposed to many people as she is very shy and skittish when meeting someone new.  With lots of treats, love and patience, she does come around and gives you her cute little underbite smile!

She would be best suited in a home with an owner that has some experience with dogs that are shy and timid.  She gets along great with other dogs and enjoys chasing her buddies around the Foster Mom's yard.

She is not fully house trained, we are working with her.  If you are interested in Simba, please complete the on-line application that can be found on our website: www.adoptmerescue.org or contact us for more information.

Local area adoption only.

Introducing Nigel! Nigel, Norris and Newt are 10 week old Lab/Collie mixes. They are currently 11-12lbs and will be a medium/large size dogs full grown. 

Nigel and his brothers were found in an industrial complex in Memphis.  There's nothing but warehouses in that area so the puppies had to have been dumped there.  Luckily a kind security guard found them and got in touch with the rescue to get these pups to safety.  

Nigel and his brothers are very friendly.  They are outgoing and social.  They are very active and energetic.  They are super playful and would love an active family that will keep them entertained and engaged in puppy friendly activities.  Nigel and his brothers are doing well in their foster home.  They are learning to be good puppies although the can and will get into puppy mischief if left to their own devices. They are good around other dogs but a but too enthusiastic for the resident chihuahua and cat.   They are 100% puppy and 100% boy! 

Nigel is up to date on age appropriate vaccines, has been tested for intestinal parasites and has been dewormed, is neutered and microchipped.  He is on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention.

As with all of our dogs, we recommend a basic obedience class to help him understand what is expected of him, and this also helps with the bonding process.

animal.description:
Scroll down to learn more about this pet:

***
Bichon and Little Buddies is open only

by appointment with a completed application.
Dogs in foster homes require an appointment and approved application to meet. The application is online at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog If a dog is listed as available, then we are still taking applications - no need to email or call to ask about the status. Note: The forms that Petfinder or Adopt-a-pet has to inquire about the dog is not our application application. Our form must be filled out to be approved to adopt a pet.***

Covid-19 Precautions:

Until further notice, Bichon & Little Buddies will be doing all meets and adoptions by appointment only. To be able to control the number of people at the shelter at one time, we will be suspending our open hours on Thursdays. If interested in adopting, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come meet the dogs you are interested in.

About this Dog:

Name: Landon Willie

Breed: Dachshund

Approximate Age: 4 yr

Gender: Male

Weight: 16 lb

Adoption Fee: $400

Why in Rescue: Texas Transfer

General Profile: Please fill out the adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog if you are interested in meeting one of our dogs.

Landon Williecame to us all the way from Texas in a snowstorm because he wanted to find a loving home. He had been adopted in Texas but returned after he dug under a fence to chase cats. Because of this, he is looking for a cat free home and one where he will be watched outside so he doesn't dig himself a path to trouble. We do not have any other history or background, so do not know if he is housetrained or lived with other pets or with children. If interested in meeting Landon Willie, please fill out the preadoption application as that is the first step in adoption. If the dog is still listed on the adoptables pages, we are still taking applications.

We do our best to evaluate the dogs while they are with us, but they sometimes act different in the shelter environment than they do in a home. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come and meet them.

If considering adopting a former breeding dog, the following article is good to read to help you understand the special needs these dogs may have. http://www.nowisconsinpuppymills.com/mill-survivors.html

Adoption Procedures:

1. Completely fill out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog. We will be checking with your vet if you have had pets, calling your landlord (if any) and checking a personal reference, before we contact you about visiting the adoptables. Any missing information may have us moving onto another application.

2. If you application is approved, we will contact you to come meet the adoptables that you are interested in.

3. If it is a match, you will complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Please be prepared to take your adopted pet home when you come meet him/her. In most cases, you will be able to take the pet home the same day. If all the vetting hasn't been done yet, we will hold the pet for you until the vet work is completed.

4. If you have filled out an application and we haven't contacted you within a week, we may have missed your application, the pet may have been adopted by another applicant, or you may have been missing information on your application. You may contact us to find out the status of your application at this time. Please give us a week to process your application before contacting us!

The adoption fee through Bichon and Little Buddies Rescue is $200 - $475 depending on the age of the dog, which includes Wi State Sales Tax. Included in this fee is your new companion who will be spayed/neutered, have a current Certificate of Veterinary Inspection (as required by state law), current on age appropriate vaccinations, heartworm tested and started on preventative, microchipped, and dewormed. Other medical needs will also have been taken care of, such as dentals and treating ear infections.

To assist you and your new pet in adjusting to life together, you will also receive an 8 week age appropriate obedience training course at For Pet's Sake Dog Training for $50 (up to $200 value). You may opt to take Puppy Kindergarten, Adult Beginners, Small Dogs Big Hearts, or Shy & Reactive Dog Class. You must start the class within 90 days of adoption for the reduced fee. For more information on the classes visit www.forpetssake.cc

All dogs are seen BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Many are in various foster homes getting extra one on one attention getting them ready for their new homes. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application. Bichon and Little Buddies is run by volunteers who have full time jobs in addition to the hours they spend with the rescue dogs. Having an application on file assures us that the potential adopter is really interested in adopting a dog. It also assists us in placing dogs in homes where both the dog and new owners are happy. The application puts you under no obligation to adopt a dog from Bichon and Little Buddies.

The Dog Pre-Adoption Application can be found at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog

Thanks for thinking about adopting your new pet!More important information:

***We are a Wisconsin based rescue and do not ship our pets. If you are considering adoption you must be willing to drive to meet and adopt the pet, as well as bring the pet back to us if the adoption doesn't work. We adopt primarily in WI and IL, but will consider applicants in MN, IA, and MI.***

***Please do not set up an appointment to meet the animals until you are ready to take your pet home. If the meeting results in a match, you can often take the dog/cat home the same day or within a couple days if the medical care hasn't been completed. We are not able to hold pets for adopters beyond this time. Thanks for understanding.***

***While we hope all of our adoptions lead to permanent homes for the animals we place, sometimes things just don't work out. We do have a 30 day trial period. For the first 30 days, if you or Bichon and Little Buddies decide that the adoption isn't a good match for either the humans or the pet, the adoption fee will be refunded minus $50 within 30 days of the return of the dog. Bichon and Little Buddies also requires adopters to return the pet to us at any time that they are unable or unwilling to care for the animal anymore.***

***We do not show dogs/cats without an appointment. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog Please do not call/email until AFTER you have filled out an application.***

Introducing Norris! Nigel, Norris and Newt are 10 week old Lab/Collie mixes. They are currently 11-12lbs and will be a medium/large size dogs full grown. 

Norris and his brothers were found in an industrial complex in Memphis.  There's nothing but warehouses in that area so the puppies had to have been dumped there.  Luckily a kind security guard found them and got in touch with the rescue to get these pups to safety.  

Norris and his brothers are very friendly.  They are outgoing and social.  They are very active and energetic.  They are super playful and would love an active family that will keep them entertained and engaged in puppy friendly activities.  Norris and his brothers are doing well in their foster home.  They are learning to be good puppies although the can and will get into puppy mischief if left to their own devices. They are good around other dogs but a but too enthusiastic for the resident chihuahua and cat.   They are 100% puppy and 100% boy! 

Norris is up to date on age appropriate vaccines, has been tested for intestinal parasites and has been dewormed, is neutered and microchipped.  He is on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention.

As with all of our dogs, we recommend a basic obedience class to help him understand what is expected of him, and this also helps with the bonding process. 

Norris's adoption fee is $475, which covers all his vetting, preventatives, fostering costs and other associated expenses.  We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Lola is approximately 4 years old and 15 lbs.  She came from an outside hoarding situation so she is currently working on her housetraining, leash walking, and enjoying human touch.  We are looking for a patient family with older children or no children, a physical fence, another confident dog, and experience with scared dogs.  These things will help keep her safe and get more comfortable as she learns how to be a companion dog in a home.  This may take month until she is totally comfortable living in a home.  This is a true rescue.

The adoption fee of $300 includes spay/neuter, rabies vaccine, distemper/parvo combination vaccine, bordetella vaccine, deworming, heartworm test, heartworm preventative, flea preventative, a dental cleaning if necessary, and a microchip.

To inquire about this dog, please select the Ask About button; include information about your family and pets, what you are looking for in a canine companion, and why this specific dog seems to be a good fit for your family; and then select the Send Email button.  Those who provide the previous information will be considered first for this canine.  We usually respond via email within 24-48 hours; please check your spam folder if you don't hear from us.  Do NOT call our center. 

Often there is very little known about our dogs' and puppies' history or even current habits. We are best guessing on breed blends. We can't guarantee there is or isn't a specific breed in their breed blend.

You can always expect to do training, regardless of whether you adopt a dog or a puppy, including crate training, house training, and basic manners. Expect a 10+ year financial, physical, and emotional commitment to this canine. We provide a variety of materials and resources to assist you with this. All dogs and especially puppies are a lot of work and a long financial commitment. Please research what it means to have a dog and make sure a dog is still going to be an important part of your life in 10-15 years. All dogs and puppies need a lot of patience and guidance.

Most dogs who are in shelters will need an adjustment period after adoption. No matter how nice our shelter is and how much attention they get from our volunteers, it is not a home and they will need time to acclimate and get rid of some nervous energy.

Hiya! Thanks for visiting me online! I'm Sophie and I’m a new arrival to Providence Animal Center from Pensacola and can’t wait to move from here into my new forever home. My adoption day is all I can think about, please don’t make me wait too long! 

The staff & volunteers are still learning about me, but so far they report that I am about 2 years old, 29 pounds and I'm ready to move into my furever home -- I'm spayed, microchipped and up to date on my vaccinations. 

I'm currently staying with fabulous foster family and they report that I am very sweet and active. She loves to play and is a master ball fetcher. She's a fan of stuffed toys, balls, raw hides... pretty much all toys! She is very cautious of new places and things, but I'm have been taking her to different parks/walks which is making her more comfortable. 

The staff feel my ideal home would have another doggie roommate to show me the ropes and help to build my confidence. She would do well in a quiet home, no city life for this girl! 

If you are interested in Sophie, please complete an adoption profile (found here: https://providenceac.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Adoption-Profile.pdf) and email it to foster@providenceac.org. I can't wait to meet you and my new best doggy friend! 

Tail wags and kisses, 

Sophie


___

During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!

Please note: Some pets are still in fabulous foster homes, so be sure to check the pet’s ‘location’ in their listing prior to scheduling an appointment. To meet a pet currently in a foster home, follow the instructions listed in their bio. Thank you for your flexibility during this challenging time! We can’t wait to see your masked face!

animal.description:
Who wants a real life teddy bear?! Meet Zack. He’s the most amazing creature and the dog version of a teddy bear. He likes to be picked up and held like a baby. Zack is dog, cat, and child friendly. He is a 1 to 2-year-old American Staffordshire terrier with a velvety fur and a wonderful personality. He likes car rides, cuddle sessions, and taking naps on his dog bed. His favorite toy is a Nyla bone. He walks while on a leash and knows a few basic commands he is also food and toy motivated. He will fit in with just about any home and any dogs owner he’s a great size and a great personality!

Our adoption fee is $260 for dogs over 5 months of age and includes all vaccinations, spay/neuter, micro chip implantation and registration/transfer, heartworm test and much more. Puppies up to 5 months of age are $275 and this includes all sets of puppy vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip implantation and registration and more. To adopt, go to www.fosterpetoutreach.org to complete an application.
Please note: Foster Pet Outreach tries to limit our adoptions to an area within approximately 60 miles of Peoria, Illinois.

animal.description:
This adorable gentleman is Pip, an 8-year-old Spaniel mix who weighs 16 pounds. He loves all people and other dogs. He especially enjoys laying right on top of his foster mom’s face. He has so much love to give! 

Pip’s adorable expression is due to past nerve damage on the one side of his face. This does not affect him; it only makes him unique in his cuteness. Pip is potty trained and will endure a crate (although he doesn't like it).  He’s had a little hair loss, so he doesn’t love the cold. Pip is happy to run outside to go potty, and then race inside for more snuggles. He also looks very dapper in cozy sweaters and jammies. 

Pip enjoys "talking," so he’d be best in a house as opposed to an apartment or condo. Pip is ready to go home and can't wait to meet his special family!

His minimum adoption fee is $255 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents. 

He has been neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

To be considered for adoption, you must first submit the application found at: 
 http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm

Jackson is an adorable terrier mix, 7 months old and weighs 12 lbs. His previous owner passed away and left him and 6 other dogs with no home and no other family to take care of him.

We believe he had not been exposed to many people as he is very shy and skittish when he meets someone new.  With lots of treats, love and patience, he does come around and then wants to play and jump in your lap!

He would be best suited in a home with an owner that has some experience with dogs that are shy and timid.  He gets along great with other dogs and has lots of puppy energy.

He is not fully house trained, we are working with him.  If you are interested in Jackson, please complete the on-line application that can be found on our website: www.adoptmerescue.org or contact us for more information.

Local area adoption only.

animal.description:
Sassy is a 9-year-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed/neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description:
Frannie is a friendly little girl who loves to play with toys and explore her surroundings. She is very happy and affectionate, and loves treats! She also loves going on walks and short hikes with her foster sibling Lloyd (pictured). She would love a medium to high energy family who can take her on outings, hikes, and other outdoor adventures.

Frannie is a dog who thrives on structure. She's very smart and motivated, and will need a strong leader to continue to provide her with the structure she is learning in her foster home. We utilize crate training with her and she needs a set schedule that includes decompressing in her crate. Without structure, she feels afraid and doesn't trust her humans. But, once she feels like she can trust you to give her direction, she is a wonderful and loyal companion. Even better to note is that Frannie is leash-trained, crate-trained, and potty-trained. Frannie is good with other calm, balanced dogs. She's the perfect dog to join your home for the new year! 

Frannie is a 3-year-old Chihuahua mix, and weighs 8 pounds. No cats or children under the age of 16. Fill out an application today to meet her!

*Bite Disclosure* Frannie was placed in an uncomfortable setting through no fault of her own and bit a human out of fear. With the proper love, guidance, and training plan (supplied by us), we don't believe she will do this again. She is a wonderful, sweet dog who just needs the right family to see how great she is! We believe in her.

animal.description: Spooky #7650 is a 5-year-old female Pit Bull mix. She is a well-rounded adult gal. She enjoys her walks 3 times a day. Spooky is housetrained. She enjoys having a toy or treat to chew on. She walks perfectly on the leash. She is good with children. She is also good with other dogs, although she may appear shy at first. If you leave food out on the counter, she will steal it! Every night, she will be in your bed with you, if you let her, either on top of or underneath the covers. Spooky doesn’t like being wet; she does not enjoy the snow or rain. However, she was well-behaved when receiving a bath. She is eager to learn and is treat-motivated. Overall, she is an amazing dog. Spooky is an LCAR momma who came to us with pups in tow. Her pups are ready for homes, and now so is Spooky! She also came to us with heartworms and ehrlichia. We are looking for someone to continue Spooky’s treatment at no additional cost to the adopter. She weighs 58 pounds and is full grown. This pup is microchipped. We believe you can always teach an ‘old’ dog new tricks, so we highly recommend continued obedience training for this smart pup; it stimulates the dog's mind and establishes a good dog/adopter relationship. This pup, like all pups, should be on heartworm preventative; an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure. If you are interested in adopting this dog, and are already approved to adopt through our organization, please contact dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with the pup’s name and ID number in the subject line. OTHERWISE, please submit an adoption application online: http://www.lastchanceanimalrescue.org/adoptus.html E-mail dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with questions. Stay tuned to our Facebook page for updates: www.facebook.com/LCARMD #adoptlove #PicMe #petsmartcharities

animal.description:
Bailey is currently on medical hold for heartworm treatment. He is accepting applications and is being fostered in MD.

What Bailey's foster mom has to say about Bailey:
Bailey’s favorite activities are snuggling, sleeping, and snuggling while sleeping. He is an affectionate, 60lb lapdog who could easily win Best Personality. A friend to everyone he meets, Bailey loves people and wants to say ‘Hi’ to every dog in his neighborhood. He is enthusiastically curious about cats too.

Bailey’s life has been difficult but you would never guess that given how outgoing and trusting he is. He is blind in both eyes although he may be able to see shadows. When he first arrived at his foster's house we thought he had neurological damage due to a (very endearing) head tilt and a mild circling gait. Even though a previous vet pointed this out as well, his current vet thinks it could be attributed to musculoskeletal alignment. Growing up, Bailey spent most of his life outdoors, chained to a refrigerator, so his body may have adapted in a way that a visit to the doggie chiropractor can assist with.

He would be best placed in a house where he won’t be left alone all day. Probably due to his rough past, Bailey suffers from separation anxiety. Living with another dog would probably be a great fit or - better yet- a work-from-home human to lay next to all day. Managing his anxiety will most likely get easier with time; Bailey is a smart guy who is very trainable and has a great memory.

Bailey was born to be someone’s dedicated and steadfast companion. He approaches the ‘man’s best friend’ moniker like it’s his job. He may be blind, but he is very empathetic and senses the kind of friend you need the moment you walk through the door. If you like to cuddle, take meandering walks, charm the pants off people, and - yes- share the warm spot on the couch, then you and Bailey would be a great fit.
BDRA has voted against the use of electrical fencing effective immediately.
animal.name: Bailey: medical hold

animal.description:
Meet Minnie! Minnie is an adorable approximately 3 year old rat terrier mix. An extremely sweet little lady, she is 16lbs and very well behaved. 

Minnie is a little timid at first but once she gains confidence in her new surroundings, she shows her sweet nature. Once she warms up, she will ask for attention, snuggles and enjoys belly rubs. She likes to hang out with her foster parents - she makes funny little noises when she wants attention and will spontaneously give you affection! 

Minnie enjoys walks but is also content to just chill. She gets along with other dogs. She is very curious about cats. This breed is not ideal with pet rabbits or Guinea pigs. Because of her small size, we would not recommend her be adopted into a home with young children. She will bark if something alarms her, but we do not consider her a ‘barker’. She does well with car rides and she will make a wonderful companion!

Minnie is house trained once she knows the routine. Sometimes she will make a funny noise and dance when it's her time to go! She is spayed, microchipped and UTD on vaccines.

To meet Minnie, please go to www.pettalesrescue.com and fill out an application. Her adoption fee is $250.00.

animal.description:
DAISY, FEMALE, 8 MONTHS OLD, 30 POUND BEAGLE/WALKER COONHOUND MIX

DAISY IS BEING FOSTERED IN THE RICHMOND VA AREA. IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN DAISY, PLEASE GO TO WWW.MOMSVA.ORG AND COMPLETE AN APPLICATION. 

Daisy is a fun and loving dog.  She has the cutest "thinking" wrinkles and curly tail.  She loves to play with her best friend Kelton.  Daisy loves to run around the yard, chew on bones and sticks, attack toys, and get lots of carrots and treats.  She loves running around, getting tackled by Kelton or playing tug of war with a rope, stick, or leftover toy . She loves carrots and frozen peanut butter in a Kong when it is time to go in her crate.  Daisy loves to go for long walks and car rides.  Daisy is working on training especially give and leave it.  Sometimes she can get a little possessive over a toy or item and by working on leave it and give  with treats, she will do great. She loves to sleep with her foster mom under the covers and stretch out.  Daisy would do great in a home with a 6ft fenced yard and another dog to play with. 

 If you are interested in adopting Daisy, please go to MOMSVA.ORG to complete an application.

animal.description:
Please only send inquires to the email in this bio all others will not be answered. Please read the bio before sending questions - we answer all we know about the dog here.

My name is Luna they say I am almost 4 yrs old and everyone who meets me thinks I am the biggest sweetheart. I want to be by my human's side or sleeping at their feet all the time. I am a loyal and obedient companion. I pick up training and commands very quickly and actually thrive on structure. I LOVE playing catch with a ball outside and rolling around in the grass. I am so excited to go out for a walk or a run because I love physical activity and exercise. My ears perk up with giddiness as the breeze blows on my nose. I'll give you tons of kisses to express how much love I have to give. I've had a very tough life but that hasn't changed my playful and charming personality. I'm extremely curious about cats so I would probably do better in a home without them. I'm just waiting for the right family to love and call my own.

Luna has her rabies vaccine and spayed/microchipped.
Shee is on flea & heartworm preventative too. I am about 50 lbs of pure love

Luna's adoption fee is $300 - obedience training is required after adoption.

Obedience training is also required for all our pups. We understand with what is going on in the world that this may be a bit delayed. Once this quarantine and Isolation period is over just email us the completion certificate.

To apply to foster or adopt adoption, please fill out application at

www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

Thank you for completing the application. We are all volunteers and short on time, we will contact you back only if we have more questions or your application is approved and you will be invited to meet the dog. We apologize for not being able to answer everyone back.

For more information contact Kelly.V@HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

DOGS are in Foster Homes. There is NO shelter.

**Our companions MUST live in your home as part of your family.**We do not transport.

**See our website for more information. www.HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

All communication is thru email so please be patient with us. We are all volunteers and work full time jobs and have families of our own.

It takes anywhere between 3-7 days to process an application - the more complete the application the easier it is for us to process it. Please notify your vet that we will be contacting them and to release information to us.

ADOPTION PROCESS:

1. The first step is to complete this application,
www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

***Everyone must submit an application - we only keep them on file for 1 month

2. Application background check, vet check, etc

3. Invitation thru email to meet the dog(s).

4. Adoption Contract

animal.description:
Miss Ellie is ready to find her forever family! <3

"Ellie is a huge cuddle bug & enjoys hanging out close to you on the couch. Her journey has made her cautious, but she has become so much more trusting and continues to improve on this daily. She likes to act like she is a lapdog. She is a very sweet dog that is eager to please and very smart."

Ellie came to us after she found herself in the shelter. Little did we know when we tagged her that we had received a surrender form for her a few months back. We were full at the time and couldn't take her. She, unfortunately, had quite the journey since then but she found her way to us anyways. Now, she never has to worry about being on her own again! 

Ellie is an almost 2-year-old female Great Pyrenees. She weighs about 63lbs but is on the thin side. Ellie is a bit reserved when she first meets people. She does warm up quickly, though. Ellie has not been to any public outings so we are unsure how she would do. Ellie has not shown to be a big chewer in her foster home. When Ellie gets really excited she does jump up on her people. She is very receptive to commands, though. Ellie does good on car rides but does occasionally try to ride upfront. She does good on a leash but could use some more working with. We are unsure how Ellie would do in an apartment setting. Ellie can be quite vocal when she hears other dogs barking or outside noises.  

Ellie has a playful personality and at other times she is pretty lazy. Ellie has not shown any interest in playing fetch. She has not had the chance to play in any water, so we are unsure if she is a water dog or not. As of right now, she seems uninterested in playing with toys. When no one is home, Ellie has free-run of the house. At night, she initially sleeps in her foster bed. Afterward, she goes to the floor or a doggie bed. Ellie is potty trained but isn't being kenneled in her foster home. 

Ellie is such a fun-loving girl! She has a great smile and is adjusting to being part of the family again! Anyone who adopts her will be super lucky! Before you welcome her home, here are some things to know. 

-Ellie is good with other dogs. She is scared of them at first, but once she warms up enjoys playing with them. 

-Ellie is not being fostered around any cats so we are unsure how she would do with them. 

-Ellie has not been around any kids. 

-Ellie does have food aggression towards the other dogs. She has gotten better, but feeding time needs to be supervised or she needs to be fed separately. 

-Ellie does resource guard a little. She has gotten better but it may be something her new family needs to watch out for. 

-Ellie is being fostered in Oklahoma City, OK. 

Ellie would like a home where she can be a lazy dog with the occasional playtimes throughout the day. She would do well in a home with other dogs with some patience or as an only dog. She has started to enjoy playing/wrestling with her foster's dogs. She is quickly improving on her trust. She has not been around kids, but I think she would be fine with them. She is not too rowdy and pretty easygoing. If this girl sounds like she belongs with you, you can apply to adopt her at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app

Her adoption fee is $225. That includes DHLPP, Rabies, and Bordatella shots. She will be micro-chipped, heart-worm tested, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered, and will be current on heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

animal.description:
Mollie is a sweet girl who loves to play fetch with anything: tennis balls, stuffed toys and even snowballs. She is endlessly curious and loves to explore. She is friendly and eager to meet new people, but quickly makes special attachments to those who give her love and attention. Mollie is potty trained and sleeps in a kennel at night at her foster home (but her foster family suspects she would rather sleep in bed with them). This intelligent pup came to her foster family already knowing how to sit and drop it. She is eager to please and eager to learn. Her foster family does not have small children but they think she would do very well with them, yet a couple of times Mollie became nippy with playing, we think some puppy training classes would fix that. She quickly calms down and generally is a very gentle soul. If you are looking for a loyal sidekick, Mollie is the gal for you!

We believe this dog is a Lab mix and was born on 9/8/20. This puppy is fostered in a private home in Lincoln. The adoption fee is $400 which covers vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter(when old enough). The adoption fee helps cover the cost of these vetting procedures. Unless the bio is marked adoption pending, s/he is still available for adoption. If youre interested in adopting this puppy, please submit an inquiry or email BraveAnimalRescue@gmail.com to ask about our adoption process (please check your spam or junk email if you do not hear back from us within a few business days). We are 100% volunteer staffed and will respond to your email as soon as possible. After you have submitted an application and been approved, we will set up a meet and greet between you and the puppy. Preference is given to applicants with a verifiable vetting history, fenced yard, and homeownership. Please be sure to follow us on Facebook and Instagram to learn more about Brave Animal Rescue and our mission.

animal.description:
Meet Stormy, the newest KPAL adoptable! Stormy is an 8-9 month old, all white Pitty mix with some light brown spots who weighs approximately 70 pounds and has BEAUTIFUL yellow eyes. 

 

Before considering adding Stormy to your family, please note that KPAL Rescue has a mandatory adoption process in place which includes a background check and a home visit. More information on our adoption process can be found in our pinned post, please read that (and this adoption post) in their entirety - our process cannot be waived. 

 

Stormy is an incredibly easy guy and a good boy. He has great manners (other than the humping that goes away with time) and is intelligent. He likes to talk to you when happy/excited, is incredibly sweet with people, and loves pets and hugs. He is average energy- will need moderate exercise but is not a marathon runner. He doesn't get upset about much - though he does have some mild anxiety about being left behind. He does not like to be left alone and will become vocal when separated from his people/dogs. He will do best in a kennel when left alone until he can be left without destruction.

 

He is friendly with other dogs but really needs some improved social skills so he can learn to be less humpy with new friends. Stormy has some basic training down but will benefit from a consistent, settled home and some work on-leash and with new experiences. He is strong, so will need an owner that can handle him and train him to walk on a leash without pulling. He is protective of the family and people coming to the door. Its possible that he was trained or encouraged to do so, but It is the only time he shows any kind of aggression. Stormy will do best in a home with no small children.

 

From Stormys foster:

Stormy should have been named Shadow because he is always right behind you. He wants to be where people are and will be a great go-everywhere dog. When he is settled, he is quite quiet and sweet. He loves bones and toys and would be a great dog to do agility work with - he has mad jumping skills. We actually really enjoy this beautiful boy and hope he will find someone that can take him along everywhere.

 

If youre interested in adding Stormy to your family, our adoption process is outlined in our pinned post and on our website: www.kpalrescue.org/pet-adoption/. Our Adoption Application can also be found on that website. 

 

KPAL Rescue dogs are fully vetted (vaccinated, microchipped, etc.) and spayed/neutered, there will be an adoption fee of $350 so that we can continue to help other animals in need. Serious inquires only, please, and feel free to share.

Meet Sweetie, an adorable 8-year-old Yorkie who weighs 10 pounds. Sweetie would stay at her special person’s side all day. She adores going for walks and lights up with excitement when she sees a leash. Sweetie loves toys, does OK in a crate (but doesn’t love it), and behaves well in the car.

Although Sweetie doesn't mind cats, she doesn't like other dogs. She needs to be the only dog in the home, and any children should be over age 12. Dogs and kids intimidate Sweetie, and she only calms down when she is away from them. 

Sweetie can bark a lot when she's startled by noises. For this reason, she would not be good for apartment or condo living. Sweetie is quiet when in a calm home. Overall, this dog is a sweetie...her name fits! She’d make someone an amazing Valentine. Sweetie is ready to go home.

Sweetie's minimum adoption fee is $265 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents.

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

To be considered for adoption, you must first submit the application found at:

animal.description:
Welcome Boe to Wags 2 Wishes foster care program!
Who is ready to give this guy the best years of his life?
Boe is a 14yr old senior Shihtzu/ Maltese mix ready to start his new life! 

Boe is a mellow little guy. He might not be a big cuddler but he does like his head and back scratched.

Boe loves meal time and treats and being outdoors. He’s usually very quiet but he likes to express his excitement over food and his foster family’s return after an outing.
 Boe loves his crate. He likes to retire to his crate at the end of the day and when he needs some time for himself. Boe chooses to exclusively sleep in his crate but he does not require crating while left alone. Boe is house trained and he will alert when he needs to go outside by pawing at the door. 
Since Boe is on the mellow side he would do best with a less active family and one without small children. Although Boe is a senior boy at 14 years old he isn’t slowing down yet. He knows there are lots of treats and head and back scratches in his future.

Boe had some big changes this year so it may tak ed him a while to warm up to his new home and people. Please he patient w our lil guy and he will turn out to be your best bud!

 * mellow dogs welcome 
* low key home environment 
* +13 yrs old kids in home 
* cats unknown 

Are you interested in giving Mr.Boe a home? Apply and the adoption specialist will contact approved apps for meets!

Apply at w2wrescue.com 
Adoption fee $150

animal.description:
ADOPTION PENDING

Meet Baxter! He is a 9-year-old, 16 lb Shih Tzu/Maltese blend boy. He is a sweet quiet boy that is used to having a dog pal around so he MUST be adopted in a home with another dog. He will also need a home where someone is home more often than not. He prefers a laid-back environment but older children (10 +) would be fine for him. He is doing well with housetraining if let out frequently. Thunderstorms are scary for the little guy so we hope his new family will comfort him. He walks well on a leash and doesn't mind car rides so he would make a great buddy to go on your errands with since he is so friendly and loves everyone he meets. His foster mom doesn't have cats but she thinks that he would get along with them if they were in his new home. He prefers to sleep in bed with his person but if he is in a dog bed, he likes to be tucked in with a blanket. He is a friendly, social boy that just needs a person to love him as much as he will love his new family. 

If you think that you have the perfect family for Baxter, please visit our website www.PoodleandPoochRescue.org where you will find an application to adopt in order to be connected to his foster mom. He is up to date on his vaccines, neutered, heartworm negative, and microchipped. His adoption donation is $300.

We do adopt out of state, but the adopter must travel to ARF to meet the dog they are looking to adopt. They must have an approved application before traveling to meet the dog. We do allow small dogs that are eligible to fly in the cabin of a plane. We DO NOT allow dogs to travel in the cargo area of the plane under any circumstances. Any dog that is adopted can of course go by personal vehicle. We do not allow dogs to be transported "pony express style" where they are passed from driver to driver.

animal.description:
*PLEASE DO NOT APPLY FOR WILLOW IF YOU DON'T HAVE A FENCED IN YARD. She is considered a fight risk and is petrified of leashes. we want to be extra careful with her for that reason .
 

 

Hi, my name is Willow. I came in from Kentucky after being found living outside on a property with a few other dogs. After a while, the rescue realized I had milk and took me back where I came from. I led the rescue right to my four puppies and they saved us all. 

Right now, Im in Pittsburgh with my foster family. At first, I was very scared of them and would hunker every time they touched me even though I wagged my tail to let them know I was sweet. 

After 8 weeks of being in my foster home, all my puppies went home and they have been helping work to bring me out of my shell. I am now crate trained, potty trained, dog friendly, and good with all humans and older kids ! I do still take a while to adjust to new surrounds and tend to be scared but once someone gives me the time I need to adjust, I come right around and am a happy go lucky pup !

 

I have two foster dog brothers ,a foster dog sister, and 2 older cats that I like to look at but don't touch! Me and my foster dog siblings can play FOREVER in the back yard. I am QUICK and zippy when I play with other dogs and smile the whole time!! My foster parent would love to see another young dog in my adopters home!

The rescue thinks Im between 1-3 years old . Im a very very sweet girl and am very content just laying around getting belly rubs all day with humans since Ive missed out on it so much ! I don't play with humans like I do my foster dog friends, I prefer being more gentle with humans 

My new owner must have a TALL fence to keep me safe because my foster parents say I'm a flight risk AND because I am REALLY scared of leashes . As soon as a leash is put on me.. I just lay down and am sad. . I dont think Id do very well with kids younger that are energetic because kids pulling my ears and poking me would REALLY scare me too much. 

If you are interested in adopting me, please submit an application from crossyourpaws.com and submit an application!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Hi my name is Minnie and I'm the cutest little puppy you'll ever meet! I am such a sweet girl, I love snuggles and kisses and just hanging out in your lap. I have the smoothest, silkiest fur around. I also love to play! I love tugging my crinkle toy with my sister and chewing on my little rubber bones. I can get a little mouthy when excited but just pop a chew toy in my mouth and I'm good to go. The first couple of nights I needed to sleep in my crate with my sister next to my foster mom's bed so I wouldn't cry. Now I can sleep through the night with my sister in our puppy pen with our crate connected without so much as a peep! I also go freely into my crate during the day to snooze when my foster mom needs to get some work done. I've been working on potty training with puppy pads and I've gotten so good that I almost always go on the pad! I like my pen nice and clean and will even use my cute little nose to fold a used puppy pad up to cover my mess. I love going outside and playing in the snow in my little jacket but with it being so cold out, I'm not able to stay out long. I haven't had a chance to use my leash yet with the cold weather. I have a bigger foster dog sister whom I love to play with. I get so excited when I get to play with her, I have no hesitation, I just jump right on in on the fun! We run around and wrestle, I'm great at listening to her doggy cues and settling down when I get too excited. I also love playing and cuddling with the kids at my foster home! They have two cats as well, they give me looks like "don't even think about it" so I just observe them from a far. Unlike some puppies, I'm able to have my food out and I just eat it as I get hungry during the day, I don't even fight over it with my sister! I enjoy getting little puppy chews. I get so excited! My sister and I run back and forth and just keep exchanging our chews, we think it's great fun!

Adoption fee includes: Full veterinary exam, alter, rabies vaccination, prepaid microchip, dewormed, Distemper combo vaccines appropriate to age, Bordetella vaccine, heartworm and flea/tick preventative while in rescue. Adoption fee:$595.00

Wyatt's adoption fee is $375 which covers his neuter, vaccinations, microchip and any additional medical care he may have needed while in the rescues care. We are a foster based rescue, we do not house dogs at a facility. Age and breed, are NLR's best guess as we often don't know who or what mom and dad are. animal.description: Hi! My name is Ivy and I am a friendly young pup. I came from warm Texas and am not exactly liking the cold MN weather. My foster mom bought me a jacket to wear outside when I have to go potty so its not super miserable. Im learning not to potty in the house but still have accidents. I like playing and getting attention from my foster family. Im the happiest when Im around them. I walk nicely on a leash, and eat my food when I get hungry. I only bark when I really need to. I really like sleeping in my kennel it makes me feel safe and protected. I try to listen to my foster mom and do exactly as she says Im learning something new everyday! Ivy's adoption fee is $375 which covers her spay, vaccinations, microchip and any additional medical care she may have needed while in the rescues care. We are a foster based rescue, we do not house dogs at a facility. Age and breed, are NLR's best guess as we often don't know who or what mom and dad are. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website www.northernlakesrescue.org

animal.description:
Please go to our website,
http://www.hoovershausealldogrescue.com/
and complete the adoption application.
MUST BE 24 YEARS TO ADOPT!!
Once your application is approved, the WI manager will call you to discuss adoption, answer questions and set up a private meet and greet if you are interested.
This process can take up to 7 days.
WE DO WEEKLY APPOINTMENTS FOR ADOPTIONS AFTER APPLICATION APPROVAL!
**OUR LOCATION: S47 W30760 HWY 59, GENESEE, WI** (corner of 59 and 83)
***CALL 262-968-3858 FOR INFORMATION***
YOU MUST COMPLETE THE ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.hoovershausealldogrescue.com
EVERY DOG IS UP TO DATE ON VACCINES FOR THEIR AGE. RABIES VACCINE IF OLD ENOUGH.
SPAYED OR NEUTERED (regardless of age) NO EXCEPTIONS
HEARTWORM and FLEA/TICK PREVENTATIVE
MICROCHIPPED
CERTIFIED VETERINARIAN INSPECTION CERTIFICATE
***WE ARE NOT OPEN TO THE PUBLIC*** ADOPTIONS ARE BY APPOINTMENT ONLY!
Amber is a Plotthound mix. She is about 7 months old as of today. (2/01/2021).
Amber is an owner surrender that moved and could not take her. She is very dog friendly and adores kids. She is doing great in her foster home learning her basic commands and leash walking. She is housebroken and crate trained.
Amber is about 35 pounds.
As always, we never guarantee the breed OR the size they'll be as an adult.
MY ADOPTION FEE is $450.00
We thank you for ADOPTING A HOOVERS HAUSE RESCUE DOG..... every dog adopted allows us to open our homes to save another!

animal.description:
*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. When your application has been processed, you will receive an email from us with further instructions on how to adopt. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting. 

At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

Amazing Grace Bully Rescue is a foster based rescue in the Pensacola, Florida area. We do not have a physical building. If you would like to meet any of our pups, the first step is to fill out our online application so we can contact you.

animal.description:
Her finder was running on the trail one day when he noticed a bright white blob from afar.As he got closer he noticed it was a gorgeous white dog with her 7 puppies! At first, he was not sure if mom was going to be protective over her babies but she surprised him by introducing herself with lots of kisses and gave him a warm welcome. The man knew he couldn't leave them all there, but also knew he couldn't carry 7 puppies by himself so he called for backup. When the man's friend showed up he had a moving box and helped load this family up. Mom was SO relieved to have finally met friendly humans that were willing to save her and her babies from the streets.
They spent the next few days in their finder's home where she was able to nap without worrying, get spoiled with toys and love and overall she and her babies were finally safe.One day, her finder and his friend loaded them all up into the car again and went for a ride. She was worried they were bringing them back to the trail where they came from but their destination was actually worse - They were at the shelter. She understood that maybe all of her puppies were too much for her finder but never expected to end up in the shelter. Thanks to our donors, though, 4P4L has arranged for these sweethearts to be transported to Colorado the second week of February.

HW+ simply means the dog has tested positive for heart worms in our screening process. We utilize what is called the fast-kill method which means we place the dog on antibiotics for 30 days and then administer 3 injections in increments afterward. The cost to treat heart worms is rather steep. However, thanks to our generous donors, we are able to cover that cost for our adopters so long as they go to our veterinarian, Red Rocks Animal Center in Lakewood.

This darling little blue heeler mix is named Dolly! She is about 10 weeks old and was found along a hwy in Montana when she was just a wee babe. She has been in our foster care since January 9, 2021 and is doing great! Dolly has a sweet demeanor and is proving to be pretty smart too! She loves the other doggies and kities in her foster home and often naps and plays with them. House training is a work in progress but she does know to follow the adult doggies out to go potty in the morning. Heelers are active and Dolly will need a family who likes to include her in their activities and stimuate her mentally as well as physically. Sweetest Girl!

Please understand that we cannot hold any pets. All adoptions are done on a first come, first adopt basis for approved applicants.

The Shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We encourage you to select your new companion by considering each dog's individual personality and pet qualities instead of relying on a breed label that is only a guess.

animal.description:
Adoptable in: MA, RI, NH, CT, and VT

Good with dogs: Yes
Good with cats: Yes, with dog savvy cats
Good with kids: Unknown
Crate trained: Mostly
House trained: Mostly

Marley is an extremely sweet and affectionate dog who loves to snuggle close to his people. Hes fairly mellow for a puppy does have some short bursts of playful energy but mostly likes to lounge with a chew toy. He is submissive and a little shy at first and is learning to build his confidence in new situations. He will sometimes freeze and/or flatten to the floor when he is overwhelmed or unsure but can be coaxed with some praise and reassurance. He is learning to walk on a leash. Marley doesnt pull but is learning not to walk directly underfoot, not to chew on the leash, and how to take leash corrections. He is very eager to please and food motivated. He has had minimal accidents in the house and will likely be housetrained quickly once he gets on a consistent schedule. He cries for 5-10 minutes in the crate when he is initially put in but settles quickly and sleeps through the night.

Marleys ideal home would be with people who have raised puppies before and can set a schedule for him to continue to progress in crate training and house training, as well as continue his leash training and teach him basic commands. Marley looks to his humans for guidance and reassurance so someone who is calm, confident and patient will be his best partner as he continues to gain confidence and settle into a new environment!

Please Note: All dogs are posted until they are officially adopted. This dog may have other interested adopters in line. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website at www.lasthopek9.org.

Questions? Please email adoptions@lasthopek9.org. For more photos, or information on upcoming adoption events where you can meet her, please go to www.lasthopek9.org or go to our Facebook page. Thank you for your interest in saving a life!

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting Zachary, please email his foster Mom Justine at jbulloc4@gmail.com

In the market for Candy Hearts this Valentine's Day season? Skip the sugar this year this year and look no further than sweet, sweet Zachary! 

Zachary has been filling his foster parents' home with his goofy, sweet nature. They have even nicknamed him Sweetie Z with all the love he has to give and will happily receive. His foster parents tell us that Zachary can be your total shadow and loves to lay by your side while you WFH all day. He *patiently* stares out the window until you're ready to get up for dinner...or play! Zachary will toss his toys around, nudge you for attention, and give lots of kisses. 

'Sweetie Z' has benefitted from his foster sister who helps to show him the ropes. While in foster, Zachary has done well seeing and greeting other dogs and shows an inquisitive nature towards making new doggo friends. While Zachary has not been seen around cats, he can be shy around other dogs that are barking or excited. 

Zachary's leash manners are well underway! His foster tells us that Zachary can be a fast walker and may even benefit from a jog every now and then. Outside of this, he does well for the most part and has high tail wags with lots of sniffs. He can pull a bit at times and does turn shy at loud noises or lots of commotion. For this reason, Zachary is best suited for a quieter environment (no hustle and bustle of a big city) and especially a house with a yard for zooms! 

Speaking of zoomies! Zachary loves to go out, in, out, in, and then back out again! Being in the backyard gives Zachary a serious case of the zooms...there is just so much fun to be had out there. His fosters write, "he does the cutest downward dog combined with a happy dance when he is excited. His whole body squirms!" Zachary's manners come into play when you can tell he wants to jump up for kisses but resists the urge and will stay down. 

Zachary would do best in a home with no young children. 'Sweetie Z' enjoys his sleep and can be a tad grumbly when he's not quite done catching Z's (or chasing tennis balls in his dreams). After he gets his beauty sleep in, he's back to his regular self with a great house-training skillset and sweet nature to boot. Additionally, Zachary would prefer to find a home where his people are around all the time...Zachary does not love to be left by himself since there is no one around to love on! 

Zachary's ideal family will greet him with patience while he settles in so he can open up on his own time. After he's confident that you've got the best couch for snuggles, you will have a lifetime of love to cash in. 

No need to keep swiping for a Valentine this year...Zachary is ready to go home with you today!

Molly is a gorgeous purebred shih tzu, 11 years old and weighs 10 pounds. She is blind, but gets around well once familiar with her surroundings. She can be hard of hearing, except when food is concerned. She is a perfect lap dog & companion. She has a quiet, calm demeanor and great disposition. Her adoption fee is $195 and covers the cost of her spay, all core vaccines (Rabies and Distemper/Parvo), a blood test to confirm Molly is in good health and teeth cleaning.

If this listing is still posted, we are still accepting applications for he/she. We do not do out-of-state adoptions on highly adoptable dogs; we would only consider out-of-state adoptions for dogs that prove hard-to-place locally. We do not hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt.

If you are interested in meeting any Poochmatch dog, please visit our website to complete an adoption application. It is in the ADOPTION folder at the top of our home page. Just fill in the blanks and SEND.
We commonly receive multiple applications for a single dog. Nevertheless, only one applicant will be invited to meet a dog on Saturday at Petsmart in Yorba Linda between noon and 3 pm OR on a mutually agreeable day, time and place during the week.

All adoption fees cover the mandatory and non-negotiable spay/neuter, rabies, microchip, microchip registration, full sets of core vaccinations (rabies and 1 set of distemper/parvo for adults, 4 for puppies) and deworming. Adoption fees vary based on age, breed, size and the costs incurred on the dog's behalf by us i.e. medical, behavioral training, etc. and they range from $295-$495.

Animal Profile: Dude is a very sweet 3 year old, 70lb Shepherd mix who joined us from Texas on January 23rd. His Texas foster reports that he is a very sweet guy and plays well with small dogs. We will post more info as we get to know him.

Foster Update: Dude is settling in well and is a very sweet natured dog. He gets along great with the resident dog. He is great on leash and walks right next to you when there are no distractions. He knows some commands like sit, come and paw but still working on his name (he's very open to a name change). He doesn't seem overly energetic, but does enjoy playing with squeaky toys. He has not been a fan of the crate but we are working on it.

Dude is still getting over kennel cough so we will not be scheduling meet and greets for a few more days.

Dude is a pretty easy going dog and we think he could make a great companion for almost any situation. He may also be a good fit for a first time dog owner, given there's interest in continuing to work with him on general obedience.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in Texas and joined us from Scarf rescue partner. This dog will be available for adoption in Seattle once evaluated.

Meet Moose, a 9-week old, 10-pound, Shepherd, Aussie Shepherd/Lab mix little guy.

Moose is a cute healthy baby, who is gentle and playful. And he’s the perfect age to teach, train and socialize. 

He’s already showing how smart he is and that he really thrives on human companionship. He is outgoing and friendly, but happiest when he can interact with the people he knows best.

He’s a high energy baby and will continue to need lots of exercise throughout his life.  If you to play games, you’ve found the perfect pal to teach and train.  
He’s sure to amaze you with how agile and talented he’ll become. 

Moose is ready and waiting to become a true animal companion, your absolute best friend.

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  Due to the young age of this puppy, he/she is not housebroken or trained unless otherwise specially indicated. All puppies require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Moose, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $550]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

animal.description:
***Please DO NOT send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available. If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder- we are still accepting applications for them***

Meet Handsome Oliver!

Oliver is a 4 year old Shepherd mix who came into the San Antonio animal shelter as a stray with a wound on his neck from an embedded collar that had to be removed & high heartworm positive. Due to both of these he quickly landed himself on the euthanasia list. We were able to pull Oliver to safety & get him seen by a vet. His neck is all healed up, he has completed heartworm treatment & he is finally ready for his forever home! 

Oliver is nervous around other dogs and will require slow introductions to any resident dogs in the home. We have had him evaluated by a trainer and he did great with other dogs! He wasn't interested in playing with them, but he was not aggressive, he was more interested in hanging out with his foster instead. He does get very excited when he sees other dogs on the leash and will pull to try and meet them! His current foster is working with him on the leash pulling, but he will require continued work in this department.

We don't have any information on Oliver with cats, but his foster said he did try to chase one in their backyard, so we are recommending a home with no cat friends. 
 
Oliver LOVES kids! When on his daily walks he gets so excited when he sees kids and pulls to get to them! He does get very excited when he meets them and tries to jump up and give them hugs. His foster is also working with him on this, but due to this and his energy level we are looking for a home with kids over the age of 10 years. 
 
Oliver is fully house broken! He only had one accident in his foster's house when he first arrived, but never since. Sometimes when dogs are transitioning to a new home, accidents will occur so patience will be key for Oliver when he first comes home with you. 

Oliver is currently the only dog in his foster home and can be a bit possessive when it comes to food so if other dogs are in the home, it will be best to feed them separately. 

Oliver LOVES his tennis balls, kong toys, & playing tug-o-war with his foster parents! He is also able to entertain himself and will play with the tennis ball for hours on end.  Oliver would love a home with an active family as this boy has some energy! 

Oliver does well in the kennel and will go in easily with treats. His foster family has not left him home alone outside of the kennel, so we're not sure how he would do free roaming while someone is not home. 
 
Lastly, Oliver's foster had this to say about him, "Overall, Oliver is a great boy with a happy personality! We have a comforter that he can sleep on, but he likes to "hide" tennis balls in it and then "find" them.  He then hikes the ball between his legs, he entertains himself with this activity at night. In addition, he tends to slobber, his tennis balls are sopping wet when he plays with them.
 
An ideal home would be one with owners who love to play with dogs.  Oliver will chase balls or play tug of war for hours.  He will drop tennis ball in your lap so you can toss it for him.  He is very capable of playing by himself, but much happier when he is playing with someone.  He has an adorable tongue that hangs out the side of his mouth when he is waiting for you to play."


***Listed BREED and AGE - We are taking our best guess on age, breed and size when fully grown. We rarely know a dog's exact age nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. ***

The first step in our process is filling out an application. We will review your application as soon as we are able- there are two of us and we do the best that we can. We review applications on a first come first serve basis and look for the best fit/match for the dog and applicant.

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Hi my name is Enchilada! I’m ~1-2 years old and 15-20 lbs! I am a bite risk. I will need an experienced owner willing to give me the time to adjust.

I just arrived to ODHS but the humans promised to update my bio as they learn more about me! 

You can still come adopt me or even join our foster program to help the humans learn all the awesome things about new dogs like me! Learn more on our website! 

Hope to see you soon! 

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

Educational articles:
3/3/3 Rule;
https://www.rescuedogs101.com/bringing-new-dog-home-3-3-3-rule/?fbclid=IwAR2iv5m7fqk3FieO7LOsstGeGsYYV_F1rJOd1BPxaImofLpcinpYsUbFRWs

Adoption Donations are $250 for an adult, $350 for puppies (a dog under one year of age), and $125 for a senior dog (based on the age of the dog). Adoption donations are to be made via cash, and credit/debit card. There is a $5 fee to run cards.

Please remember to bring a collar and leash (non-retractable) with you the day of the adoption. Note: Martingale collars and slip leads are strongly recommended.

Due to COVID19, we aren't having as many open, public adoption events.  Current schedule is pre-determined meet and greet appointments are Wednesday evenings and on Saturdays. 
Our adoption center is located at 3602 Lafayette Blvd, Suite 102, Fredericksburg, VA 22408. It's important that you keep an eye on your emails for any changes or updates during the adoption process.

Visit our website for an application to adopt. 
https://www.olddominionhumanesociety.org/adoption-application

Old Dominion Humane Society is a volunteer based organization. We are run completely by volunteers, who also have full time jobs, so we appreciate your patience.  Currently, the average timeframe for a response to your application is 1 week.

Like us on Facebook "Old Dominion Humane Society"
and be a part of promoting forever homes for dogs in need.
#Adopt #Donate #Foster #Volunteer 

Note: ODHS only adopts to Virginia and surrounding states (including D.C.). A $50 out of state fee applies.
