animal.description:
Breed: Rough Coated Patterdale Terrier (Fell Terrier)
Sex: Male
DOB: ~12/29/2017
Weight: 32 lbs
Energy Level: Medium-High
Personality Type: Sweet, Timid, People-Oriented, Treat Motivated, Playful!
History: Transferred from another shelter
Good With: Kids 8+ years, Dogs
Ideal Home: Active home willing to work with Jacques on his leash manners!
Fence Requirements: Required
Special Info: Jacques has a low-shed wirey coat!

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Meet Samus (we call him Sam for short). He's a sweet and energetic little guy who loves to be outside. He took a few days to warm up to his foster family but now he sticks around us like velcro. He's taken some notes from our lazy couch potato dog and he's starting to love his belly rubs and nap time. He sleeps through the night in a crate but will start to stir in the early morning. He's also happy to plop into bed with us and sleep like a log!

He was initially very 'into' our female dog but since his neuter he respects her personal bubble. Early on he had a couple of accidents in the house but he's generally been good about keeping his business outdoors. He loves his walks and he's well-behaved on the leash to boot.

He's a skinny little thing so we've been adding some healthy snacks like chicken and rice along with his kibble so that he puts on a few pounds, which he's been very happy about!

Sam is a good little pup who gets along with the other dogs and people he's been introduced to (unsure about cats). He'd be a great addition to any household, especially one with other dogs that he can go on walks and play with.

Samus is a Male Long-haired Dachshund/Terrier Mix that we estimate to be around 4 years old and weighs 13 lbs.

animal.description:
**Please read Kenra's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

Here's Kenra, an 18-month old, 33-pound, Yellow Lab/Hound mix young lady, who is a bundle of energy.

Kenra  is one of the friendliest gals around.  She loves the company of humans and is eager to please them. She enjoys following her foster family around and staying close to where they are. She likes "talking" to them a lot as well.

She has an amazing sense of smell and will literally follow a scent for hours.
  
And she loves adventures and trying out lots of new activities. She’s energetic and athletic and will enjoy hiking, camping and swimming.

She’s tailor made for an active family who loves to have fun and has the time to train a young, energetic dog.

Kenra had heartworm when she first came into foster care, but has been treated and has recovered and is now well.

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Kenra, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

animal.description:
****Please DO NOT message the rescue asking if this puppy is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. The first step in our adoption process is to fill out an adoption application at www.snarrnortheast.org. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO & FAQs BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Ferdinand
*Age: 5 months
*Current Weight: 43 pounds
*Rescued from: Texas
*Adoption fee: $495 (plus $125 spay/neuter deposit, which is refundable when spay/neuter agreement is fulfilled)
*Health: up to date on puppy shots so far (adopter will be responsible for remaining puppy vaccinations)

This handsome, sweet boy is very special and he is looking for his perfect home.  Ferdinand was born onto a property with several dogs living on chains.  But several ladies banded together to free him from this certain destiny of living on a chain.  We are always said to leave dogs to live this life but grateful to have this super sweet boy in our care and ready to find his perfect home.  Ferdinand is a sensitive boy, he's great with other dogs and kids.  Of course, the kiddos at his level better be ready for some puppy kisses.  Ferdinand sleeps on his bed by his foster's bed.  He loves toys, belly rubs and sharing time on the sofa with his people.  He is a big puppy so we expect him to be a big boy.  Ferdinand is doing great with his potty training.  Ferdinand is looking for a home with a fenced in yard and another friendly canine to play with would be awesome.  If you are looking for a big snuggle buddy that will melt your heart this Valentine's day, Ferdinand is your boy. 

Ferdinand was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. He will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on January 17th ready for adoption! 

IMPORTANT: This puppy has not yet been altered. For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a strictly-enforced signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

To apply to adopt a puppy from this litter, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications.  

**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**
We do recommend listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice when applying for puppies with several littermates.
(Littermates: )

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
Meet Clifford! This dog has the most beautiful eyes and a heart of pure gold!  He is a terrier mix with beautiful brindle coloring and he weighs about 15 pounds. He is 2 to 3 years old. We found Clifford laying on the floor of a kill shelter near the Mexico border. He was crippled and could not walk so we rescued him and took him to our vet. We discovered that Clifford had two broken legs on opposite sides of his body. His x-rays were sent to a specialist who is an expert in plate repairs and he agreed that he could help Clifford. He has had his surgery and as you can see in the video, doing remarkably well! He will be released for full activity on Feb 8th and we can't wait to see him running full speed through the yard. Clifford loves everyone so would make a great addition to any family.

For more on Cliffords story, please view our Facebook page. https://www.facebook.com/TracysPawsRescue


Clifford is located in a wonderful foster home in San Antonio. We will arrange a time to meet Clifford once your application to adopt him has been approved.  He is neutered, up to date on all shots, microchipped and his adoption fee is $300.  If you would like to add Clifford to your family, please complete an application here-

https://www.tracyspawsrescue.org/adoption-application

Services our dogs receive prior to adoption:
Chagas Testing
Heartworm Testing (age appropriate)
Tick Illness Testing (age appropriate)
All age appropriate vaccines
Heartworm and flea/tick preventatives 
Spay/neuter surgery 
Microchip

* The breed(s) listed are guessed and based on the dog's physical appearance *

animal.description:
Courtesy Post!
Milo is with his owner. If after reading Milo's post, you are interested in adopting him, please contact his owner directly as listed in this post. 

Milo
4 years old
Neutered male
24lbs

Per owner: 
Milo is a very sweet and energetic dog. He would do well in a home with a backyard for him to play in everyday. His new owner must be vigilant on walks. Milo is reactive towards other dogs. If he's running or distracted when the dog is approaching, he will be fine. He has recently become reactive towards our other dog in our home and even started to bite so he NEEDS to be the only dog in the home. He has never been aggressive towards people though and will give kisses to all who accept them. He is also quite good at giving hugs and is easily stimulated with toys and bones. There is no doubt that whoever adopts him will fall in love with him as his owners have. 
If you can meet Milo's needs and you can give him a home where he can be the only dog, please contact Melissa at mrparker192@gmail.com
